President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Mark M. Boulware is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Chad, Christopher J. McMullen is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Angola, Joseph A. Mussomeli is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Slovenia, Wanda L. Nesbitt is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Namibia, and Karen Brevard Stewart is nominated for Ambassador to the Lao People's Democratic Republic. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Helen Hurcombe, Kathleen Martinez, and Pamela C. Schwenke to the Committee for Purchase from People Who are Blind or Severely Disabled.